&lt;p&gt;Oxford Haemophilia &amp; Thrombosis Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 3 Assistant Coordinator - Anticoagulation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed Term 37.5 hrs/week each&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oxfordshire Anticoagulant Service is located within the Oxford Haemophilia and Thrombosis Centre at the Churchill Hospital and manages approximately 6000 patients taking warfarin in the community. We are a small friendly multidisciplinary team providing testing and advice for patients on all aspects of anticoagulant care and are currently looking to appoint Band 3 clerical officers to work primarily in the anticoagulation service but to also provide support to the secretarial and administrative team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the multidisciplinary team you will work closely with nurses and laboratory staff under the supervision of the anticoagulation team leaders. The core role of the post is to ensure that patient dosing information is accurately provided to patients, clinicians and other health care workers, and that all documentation and electronic information is recorded and maintained to the highest standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The core working hours of the service are Monday to Friday between 9:00 -17:00, but working outside the core hours may be required to meet the needs of the service. Both full and part-time applicants will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 13/11/20&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namesharon osborneJob titleAdmin and Access Team LeaderEmail addresssharon.osborne@ouh.nhs.ukTelephone number01865 225300&lt;/p&gt;
